title: Acer platanoides - Schwedler Norway maple
description: Schwedler Norway maple is commonly cultivated in Bozeman, Gallatin County, Montana. This site lies in a neighborhood on South Tracy Avenue. The purplish leaves especially during the early to middle summer are distinctive of the Schwedler cultivar. Photos were take during June 2022 except for those showing fall leaf colors, which were taken during October 2022 (the day before heavy snows).
label: Original
